      • getTimeSensitivity

        public final java.time.Duration getTimeSensitivity​()
        Description copied from interface: RateMeter
        A time sensitivity which affects the behaviour of RateMeter.tick(long, long) method in a way that allows registering a sample at an instant that differs from the specified one not more than by the time sensitivity.

        This behavior may be observed via RateMeter.rightSamplesWindowBoundary(). Hence this method can be considered as an important implementation detail leaked through RateMeter's leaky abstraction.

        Implementation considerations
        It is recommended to use a resolution (accuracy, granularity) of the timer used by a user of RateMeter. For example 200ns may be a good approximation of the System.nanoTime() accuracy (see timers-bench and Nanotrusting the Nanotime for measurements and explanations).

        Specified by:
        getTimeSensitivity in interface RateMeter<S>
        Returns:
        A positive, i.e. not negative and not zero time sensitivity which is used internally.

      • tick

        public final void tick​(long count,
                       long tNanos)
        Description copied from interface: RateMeter
        Registers a sample of count ticks at tNanos instant. If tNanos is greater than current RateMeter.rightSamplesWindowBoundary() then this method moves the samples window such that its right boundary is at tNanos.
        Specified by:
        tick in interface RateMeter<S>
        Parameters:
        count - Number of ticks. May be negative, zero, or positive. If zero then the method does nothing, otherwise adds count to the currently registered number of ticks at the specified instant, or just remembers count ticks if no ticks were registered at the specified instant.
        tNanos - An instant (a pair (startNanos, elapsedNanos)) at which count ticks need to be registered.

      • rateAverage

        public final double rateAverage​(long tNanos)
        Description copied from interface: RateMeter
        Calculates an average (mean) rate of ticks (measured in samplesInterval-1) from the start till the tNanos, if tNanos is greater than RateMeter.rightSamplesWindowBoundary(), otherwise returns RateMeter.rateAverage().
        Specified by:
        rateAverage in interface RateMeter<S>
        Parameters:
        tNanos - An effective (imaginary) right boundary of the samples window.
        Returns:
        Average rate of ticks or 0 if tNanos is equal to RateMeter.getStartNanos().

      • rate

        public final long rate​()
